## Research & Professional Experience

### **Graduate Researcher**, African Institute for Mathematical Sciences (AIMS) | 2023 – Present
*   Developed a novel **hybrid Minkowski-Log-Cosh loss function** to enhance the robustness of LSTM networks for time-series forecasting on noisy data.
*   Applied and evaluated deep learning models on a 10-year public health dataset (2013-2023) to forecast malaria incidence, addressing challenges in epidemiological forecasting.
*   Demonstrated significant improvements in model robustness and predictive accuracy over traditional loss functions in the presence of outliers.

### **Undergraduate Researcher**, Universite de Kara | 2021 – 2022
*   Designed and implemented Artificial Neural Network (ANN) models for agricultural yield prediction, integrating climate and soil variables.
*   Conducted research evaluating the socio-economic impact of online learning during the COVID-19 pandemic on the student population.
*   Performed comprehensive feature sensitivity analysis to identify and rank key drivers of crop productivity.

